means.word_mean: 相反的,不一致的,对立的

derivation.yuyuan_name: late Middle English: from medieval Latin incompatibilis, from in- 'not' + compatibilis (see compatible)

entry.tran: 不能和谐相处的;不协调的;不一致的
entry.def: If one thing or person is incompatible with another, they are very different in important ways, and do not suit each other or agree with each other.

example.ex: They feel strongly that their religion is incompatible with the political system...
example.tran: 他们强烈感受到他们的宗教信仰与政治体制不相称。

example.ex: His behavior has been incompatible with his role as head of state...
example.tran: 他的行为与他的国家领袖身份不相称。

entry.tran: 不兼容的;不相容的;互斥的
entry.def: If one type of computer or computer system is incompatible with another, they cannot use the same programs or be linked up together.

example.ex: This made its mini-computers incompatible with its mainframes...
example.tran: 这就使得它的微型计算机与它的大型主机不兼容。

example.ex: Many institutions exchange information by hand because of incompatible computer systems.
example.tran: 由于计算机系统不兼容，许多机构通过人工方式进行信息交换。
